headline: Who was Quentin Deranque, the far-right activist killed in Lyon?
description: The 23-year-old activist, who died on Saturday, February 14, after a fight in the streets of Lyon, was an integralist Catholic drawn to the idea of 'self-defense' who embodied the new generation of France's far right.

headline: Iran and US agree on 'guiding principles' for a deal, say Iranian officials
Russian and Belarusian athletes permitted to compete under national flags at 2026 Paralympics
Storms decimate thousands of puffins on France's Atlantic coast
description: Hit especially hard by recent storms, the birds have been washing ashore by the thousands along France's Atlantic coast. A rescue center in the southwest is taking in those who managed to survive conditions not seen in over a decade.

headline: At Navalny's grave, two years after his death in a Russian prison: 'We are not alone'
description: Several hundred supporters of the Kremlin's most renowned opponent gathered on Monday at the Moscow cemetery where he is buried. A new investigation confirmed the cause of his death: assassination by poisoning.

headline: Chinese kung-fu robots steal the show in world's most-watched TV program
description: Watched by 600 million viewers, the annual gala broadcast by national television channel CCTV for Lunar New Year's Eve serves as a showcase for China's advances in robotics and artificial intelligence.

headline: 'Marty Supreme,' with Timothée Chalamet: An existential and frenetic table tennis journey
description: Director and screenwriter Josh Safdie, now working apart from his brother Benny, gives the 'Dune' star the standout role of his career as a brash table tennis player inspired by Marty Reisman.

The Epstein case: Thirty years of judicial negligence, at the expense of victims
description: The first complaints against the millionaire date back to 1996. Yet between his initial conviction in 2008 and his arrest in the summer of 2019, he was never troubled by the justice system.

headline: In substance, Rubio's message in Munich was the same as Vance's
description: While the US secretary of state struck a less aggressive tone toward Europe than the American vice president had a year earlier, the substance of the speech changed little.

headline: Agnès Delahaye, historian: 'The Minneapolis protests are part of the major historical social struggles in the US'
description: In an interview with Le Monde, the historian said that Donald Trump's narrative of a white America radiating power is intended to erase the complexity of a multicultural past shaped by violence and struggles for emancipation.
